SECURE SPREAD is a software package that is intended to provide secure 
group communications and reliable multicast services across local and wide 
area networks such as the Internet. SECURE SPREAD includes computer 
software and may include associated media, printed materials, and ``online'' 
or electronic documentation. By installing, copying or otherwise using
SECURE SPREAD, you agree to be bound by the terms of this License. Read its
terms very carefully. If you do not agree to these terms, do not install or 
use SECURE SPREAD.

This License is granted by the copyright owners of SECURE SPREAD: 
The Johns Hopkins University.

SECURE SPREAD is protected by the copyright laws of the United States
of America and international copyright treaties.

This software uses a Blowfish implementation that is derived from
Blowfish code written by Bruce Schneider ().
